1. Dockerfiles are used to create docker images
2. They are small programs to create an image
3. To build any docker image from Dockerfile run following command
	docker build -t name-of-result .
where . represents the current path of Dockerfile

4. And the resultant image will be stored in local docker registry.
5. while making image from dockerfile, docker keep the cache of lines that does not changed
6. Dockerfiles are not shell script


